      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "[`QCharRef QString::operator[](int position)`](https://doc.qt.io/qt-5/qstring.html#operator-5b-5d):\r\n\r\n> **Note:** Before Qt 5.14 it was possible to use this operator to access a character at an out-of-bounds position in the string, and then assign to such a position, causing the string to be automatically resized. Furthermore, assigning a value to the returned `QCharRef` would cause a detach of the string, even if the string has been copied in the meanwhile (and the `QCharRef` kept alive while the copy was taken). These behaviors are deprecated, and will be changed in a future version of Qt.",
      "created_at" : "2020-02-09T14:56:07Z",
      "html_url" : "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/18080#issuecomment-583854231",
